  "_field_note": "maxCrawledPlacesPerSearch reduced from 80 → 60 because 180 strings × 80 = 14,400 max places (too much). 180 × 60 = 10,800 max — after dedup yields ~3,500-5,000 unique businesses across 12 sectors (~300-400/sector average for high-density sectors, fewer for niche). enrich.py with --mode solo filters to top buyable-profile per sector. scrapeContacts pulls emails + socials (extra credits but worth it for outreach). scrapePlaceDetailPage must stay true to get website/phone/category reliably. Niche sectors (office plant care, mat rental, document destruction) will naturally yield fewer than 60/search and that's fine — it's the sourcing-reality signal we want.",

  "_solo_track_deal_box": "Target $300-500k purchase price. SDE floor ~$253k at $300k → ~$286k at $500k. Revenue floor ~$843k-$952k at 30% margin. Smaller deal than Dan track ($500k-$1M) because no Dan CPA cover + simpler operationally. See context/acquisition.md for full deal box.",

